comment.narrative:
- 3 (Law of the Republic of Tajikistan on the Prevention of Domestic Violence; On State Guarantees of Equal Rights for Men and Women and Equal Opportunities for their Implementation; Law “On Legal Normative Acts of the Republic of Tajikistan” Recommendation provided to draft of Anti-discrimination law);
- 6 (2 TV programme, 4 radio programms)  media campaigns to discuss gender stereotypes and violence and discrimination against women have been conducted; 

- 3 (1 National; 2 sub-national coordination meetings) dialogue meetings for improved monitoring and coordination on implementation of the Police Reform have been conducted;
- 26 cases (2 male, 24 female) of domestic violence have been referred to MDWG for consideration and support;

- 6 (3 action plans were developed by Community Policing Partnership Teams and 3 by women and youth group to address the harmful gender norms);
- 62 prosecutors, 49 judges, 50 lawyers, 73 police officers and 19 bailiffs have been trained;
- 370 persons (304 women, 64 men and 2 children) have received shelter, legal advice, psycho social consultations, medical, social and other services provided by sectoral referral mechanisms in selected districts.
